article.description: — B.J. Mack totaled 18 points and 11 rebounds and Wofford rolled to a 77-60 victory over Hampton in nonconference play Friday night.
article.headline: Mack's double-double leads Wofford over Hampton 77-60
article.linkText: Mack's double-double leads Wofford over Hampton 77-60
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- — B.J. Mack totaled 18 points and 11 rebounds and Wofford rolled to a 77-60 victory over Hampton in nonconference play Friday night. Max Klesmit had 16 points for the Terriers (3-1), while Messiah Jones and Ryan Larson scored 13 and 10, respectively. Russell Dean and Mario Haskett Jr. led the Pirates (2-2) with 15 points apiece. Dean added eight rebounds. DeAngelo Epps scored 11. Najee Garvin, the Pirates' leading scorer entering the matchup at 17 points per game, shot only 20 percent for the game (2 of 10). ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
